Hi.
Apologies if this has been posted already.
After about 10 minutes of using my sound, it stops working. 
My card as reported by the kernel:
Mar 27 14:15:09 mct12 kernel: ad1848/cs4248 codec driver Copyright (C) by
Hannu 
Savolainen 1993-1996
Mar 27 14:15:09 mct12 kernel: Found OPL3-SAx (YMF719)
Mar 27 14:15:09 mct12 kernel: <MS Sound System (CS4231)> at 0x534 irq 5
dma 0,1
After a bit of use (10-20 minutes xmms etc) I get a lot of these error
messages whenever I try to play anything:
Mar 27 15:38:30 mct12 kernel: Sound: DMA (output) timed out - IRQ/DRQ
config error?
Mar 27 15:38:31 mct12 kernel: ad1848: Auto calibration timed out(1).
Mar 27 15:38:31 mct12 kernel: ad1848: Auto calibration timed out(3).
Mar 27 15:38:31 mct12 kernel: Sound: DMA (output) timed out - IRQ/DRQ
config error?
Mar 27 15:38:32 mct12 kernel: ad1848: Auto calibration timed out(1).
Mar 27 15:38:32 mct12 kernel: ad1848: Auto calibration timed out(3).
Mar 27 15:38:34 mct12 kernel: ad1848: Auto calibration timed out(1).
Mar 27 15:38:34 mct12 kernel: ad1848: Auto calibration timed out(3).
Mar 27 15:38:34 mct12 kernel: Sound: DMA (output) timed out - IRQ/DRQ
config error?
etc etc
All the sound drivers are modules...
Linux mct12.nettas.telstra.com.au 2.3.99-pre3 #2 Mon Mar 27 09:48:20 EST
2000 i686 unknown
Kernel modules         2.3.10
Gnu C                  2.95.2
